stifying of rich empirical and theoretizing research into the social aspects of language variation. Taking a broad view on Cognitive Sociolinguistics, the volume covers three main areas: corpus-based research on language variation, cognitive cultural models, and the ideologies of sociopolitical and socio-economic systems.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aCognitive grammarxSocial aspects. 0aSociolinguistics. 4aKognitive Linguistik. 4aSoziolinguistik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aCognitive Linguistics.  asociolinguistics.1 aBerthele, Raphael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDirven, René, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDirven, René, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFiksdal, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGeeraerts, Dirk, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGries, Stefan Th., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrondelaers, Stefan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeylen, Kris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJanicki, Karol, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoller, Veronika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKristiansen, Gitte, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKristiansen, Gitte, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMorgan, Pamela S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPolzenhagen, Frank, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSharifian, Farzad, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 